  see also  references  external links historyedit flir took its name from the acronym for forwardlooking infrared the company began in  with airborne ir systems and developed from  to  through product development and acquisitions of related companies originally based in tigard oregon the company relocated to portland in the mids flir teamed up with hughes aircraft company in  with hughes taking part ownership of flir the company became publicly traded in a june  ipo which raised  million for the company with shares offered at  in  the company had grown to sales of  million annually the next year j kenneth stringer iii was named as president of the company the company bought swedens agema infrared system in  which doubled the size of the company acquisitions continued the following year when they purchased inframetrics inc of massachusetts for  million the companys president and chief executive officer kenneth stringer iii was fired by the board of directors in may  due to errors in the companys accounting practices in september  the securities and exchange commission sec sued flir over accounting irregularities the next year three executives at the company were charged with fraudulent accounting related to the sec case that included claims of inflated sales sales at flir grew to  million in fiscal year  in  the company bought a building in wilsonville from mentor graphics for  million for use as a new headquarters in  flir acquired indigo systems a leading developer and supplier of a wide range of infrared imaging products including cooled and uncooled infrared detectors camera cores and finished cameras beginning in  the company began supplying bmw with imaging technology for use on the luxury automakers vehicles also in  flir was named the th fastestgrowing company on cnnmoneys list of the  fastestgrowing tech companies in  flir was listed as the rd best small business by forbes the previous year they were ranked th that july flir announced a sevenyear contract worth up to  million with the united states army for cameras to be installed on helicopters entrance to company headquarters in wilsonville oregon which is adjacent to the mentor graphics campus in march  the company reported that it would restate its financial statements for the period from  to  primarily to record noncash charges for compensation expense relating to past stock option grants flir was also sued by investors over these same allegations the company purchased extech instruments corp in october  for  million the next month flir executed its third stock split flir made another acquisition in april  when it purchased ifara tecnologias of spain for about  million for the  fiscal year the company recorded  billion in sales a record for the company on january   flir was added to the sp  stock index replacing national city corporation flir was named as the northwests top company by the seattle times in  the third time the company was at the top  and  it sold extech data systems a division of extech which made portable printers in december  and bought the security hardware maker directed perception that month for  million flir continued to grow via acquisitions when it purchased bankrupt raymarine in may  for  million in december of  flir acquired lorex technology inc for approximately  million on november   flir announced that it had acquired dvtel inc a leader in software and hardware technologies for advanced video surveillance for approximately  million in cash in december  flir acquired prox dynamics the makers of the black hornet a nanodrone used by the military and law enforcement for surveillance and reconnaissance for  million operationsedit headquartered in wilsonville oregon the company also has manufacturing and rd facilities in goleta near santa barbara california north billerica a suburb of boston massachusetts tel aviv israel bozeman montana stillwater oklahoma freeport pennsylvania oak ridge tennessee west lafayette indiana tallinn estonia täby sweden fareham uk and west malling uk worldwide flir employs in excess of  people with more than  located in the united states the company is structured to focus on six specific business segments the surveillance group addresses highend military and other governmental thermal imaging markets the instruments segment produces thermography cameras for building inspection predictive maintenance and rd as well as test and measurement tools development of oem camera cores and components new technologies and new applications for existing technologies are served by the oem  emerging markets group marine electronics including thermal cameras under both the flir and raymarine brands fall under the maritime segment thermal and visible light cameras for industrial commercial and residential security are serviced under the lorex by flir brands by the security segment the detection segment produces sensors for chemical biological radiation and explosive detection see alsoedit list of companies based in oregon referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j flir systems financials   a b flir systems sec filing k december    flir systems inc the oregonian july   pp d   colby richard january   thermal imaging heats up the oregonian pp c   a b francoeur david about flir systems retrieved june     a b flir wins hughes marketing deal the oregonian august   p c   a b c the bottom line briefcase chief financial officer advances to presidency of flir systems the oregonian april   p b   the oregonian  the oregonian june   pp n   briefcase flir system incs first offering of stock brings in  million the oregonian june   pp d   earnings flir pays onetime charge of  million in quarter the oregonian january   pp b   the bottom line briefcase flir systems inc doubles in size with completion of acquisition the oregonian december   pp b   yim sujin december   portlands flir systems signs pact to acquire rival the oregonian pp b   woodward steve may   flir systems removes top executive the oregonian pp b   a b