 facebook linkedin twitter print in our local heroes series flir likes to highlight the stories of law enforcement and first responders using flir products in their daytoday lives by highlighting them as our “local heroes” on a monday morning in early june the corpus christi fire department hazmat crews in southern texas were called to a scene after receiving reports of a strong ammonia smell throughout a widespread area the ccfd hazmat crew used a flir thermal camera capable of visualizing a leak that would otherwise be invisible to the naked eyethe plume of ammonia was made visible to the hazmat crew allowing them to locate and evaluate the source of the leak and stop the flow of ammonia to avert a larger crisis watch the video below and head here to see the full story learn more about flir’s optical gas imaging cameras here recent posts what do  million bats look like in thermal flir maritime introduces first cooled thermal camera to awardwinning mseries line flir m celebrating  years of innovation a history of aerial observation flir thermal snake feeding flir systems introduces highperformance raymarine axiom pro multifunction displays flir receives “red dot best of the best”  award for flir exxseries categories hot topics product news featured top feature all comments electrical  mechanical   flir tg flir cseries flir e e e  e flir e e  e flir e e  e flir t t  t flir tseries flir t t t  t flir tk test  measurement tools ir windows   building   flir cseries flir e e e  e flir ebx ebx  ebx flir e e  e flir tbx tbx tbx  tbx flir tseries flir tk test  measurement tools   test  measurement   flir dm imaging multimeter flir tg spot thermal camera flir tg spot thermal camera flir mr imaging moisture meter flir mr imaging moisture meter flir mr imaging moisture meter flir flexible clamp meters flir dm digital multimeter flir dm digital multimeter flir cm power clamp flir cm power clamp flir cm power clamp flir cm clamp with ir thermometer flir vp voltage detector flir